              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". Consisting of 45 micron thick surface barrier",
                "Delta-E detector,and a 1.7 mm thick Si(Li) E-detector",
                "for LCP-detection and identification."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". Two 30 micron surf.barrier detectors, perpen-",
                "dicular to neutron beam, one of them in line with",
                "Delta-E and E-detectors  for fragment detection."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The work is concerned with ternary fission in which",
                "the third particle (LCP) is emitted in the direction",
                "of one of the fission fragments ('polar emission').",
                "In this experiment, two cases are distinguished",
                "    'L-emission' ... the LCP is emitted in the direct-",
                "ion of the light fragment  and",
                "    'H-emission' ... the LCP is emitted in the direct-",
                "ion of the heavy fragment."
              ]
            }
          ],
